Fujifilm is set to launch its “instax SQUARE SQ6” camera, which is compatible with square format film. The SQ6 is an analogue camera which allows users to print photos on-the-spot using Fujifilm’s instant film, and offers users numerous shooting functions and a small form factor. The camera has an automatic exposure adjustment function that is activated when the shutter button is pressed, detecting the ambient brightness and adjusting to provide the optimum shutter speed and flash intensity. The SQ6 also features a selfie-mode, where the settings will be adjusted to optimise the focus for selfie images. The camera also features: The SQ6 will be available on 25 May 2018 for $130.   